description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Service Manager in the Perioperative and theatre services based at St Bartholomew’s Hospital. The Cardiothoracic Surgery services are one of the largest in Europe and there is the opportunity to work alongside world class clinical teams within the Barts Heart Centre &amp; Barts Thorax Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced operational manager, secondary care experience is a must &amp; experience of managing surgical services is desired but not essential. Post holders will require strong analytic skills, experience of managing RTT &amp; Cancer Access Targets and experience of managing large administrative teams is desirable. This is a busy role with opportunities to gain exposure in budget management, coding &amp; writing business cases. If you wish to develop your career down a General Management route this role would give excellent operational experience to give you that grounding.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 27th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Alicia Housego for any questions about the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;E: alicia.housego@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;T: 07776227645&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAlicia HousegoEmail addressalicia.housego@nhs.netTelephone number07776227645&lt;/p&gt;
